cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SE, cs.DC

The paper discusses hardware Trojan detection and prevention techniques, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The use of new design techniques and memory technologies also suggests a potential overlap with embedded systems (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the approach on the synthesis, place-and-route, and fabrication of ICs, which falls under the category of digital circuits (cs.DC).
